response_text: Notice when your inner critic speaks. Try answering it with kindness rather than judgment.
Notice five things you can see, four you can touch, three you can hear — this can help ground you in the now.
Anxiety waves come and go. What would it feel like to let this wave pass without fighting it?
It’s okay to hold onto memories and also allow new moments into your life.
If you are thinking of harming yourself, please reach out to a helpline or trusted person right now. You matter.
Every setback you’ve faced has brought you here. You are stronger than you think.
Gently bring your attention to each part of your body. Notice sensations without needing to change anything.
Anger is a valid signal. What’s the need or boundary beneath it?
You are not as alone as you feel. Can you reach out to someone, even just with a small message?
You are already enough, even when you fall short of your own expectations.
